Let's spin up a dummy pod and create a mock tarball directory so you can practice the workflow.

kubectl run kiwi --image=nginx:1.21.6
mkdir -p /root/image-archive
# In the real exam, the actual image tarballs will be here. 
# We will just create a dummy file for syntax practice.
touch /root/image-archive/nginx_1.21.6.tar

--

Solution

bom generate --image-archive /root/image-archive/nginx_1.21.6.tar --format json --output /root/kiwi-sbom.spdx

INFO bom v0.7.1: Generating SPDX Bill of Materials 
INFO Processing image archive /root/image-archive/nginx_1.21.6.tar 
FATA generating doc: scanning image archives: generating tarball package: extracting tarball to temp dir: sampling bytes from file header: EOF 